<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 14 at 2:32AM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...HEAT INDEX VALUES UP TO 110 DEGREES THIS AFTERNOON...
The combination of abnormally hot temperatures and supportive dew
points temperatures will produce heat index values up to 110
degrees for a few hours this afternoon. A few locations may
briefly experience heat index values a degree or two above 110
degrees.
If spending time outside today, drink plenty of water, wear light
weight and light colored clothing, and take frequent breaks from
the heat. Young children and pets should never be left unattended
in vehicles. This is especially true during warm or hot weather
when car interiors can reach lethal temperatures in minutes.</description>
